{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "rbac-bootstrap-e2e",
    "name": "RBAC – Bootstrap (POST /api/v1/owner/bootstrap)",
    "description": "E2E tests for POST /api/v1/owner/bootstrap.\n\nFolder execution order (orchestrated by make e2e-rbac):\n  1. setup                — register + fetch Gmail OTP + verify email + login + GET /me\n                           (captures bstrp_access_token and bstrp_happy_id)\n  2. auth-guard           — 401 without Authorization header (JWT guard)\n  3. validation           — 422/400/413 input-error cases (authenticated; fires before secret check)\n  4. secret-guard         — 403 wrong bootstrap_secret (authenticated; fires before service)\n  5. happy-path           — 201 + body shape + role_name checks (consumes the one-time slot)\n  6. owner-already-exists — 409 after a successful bootstrap (owner guard)\n  7. rate-limiting        — IP limiter exhaustion: 3 warmups, 4th → 429 (Redis flushed first)\n\nRoute: POST /api/v1/owner/bootstrap\nGuard order (handler): JWT auth → body decode → validate secret non-empty → compare secret → service\nRate limit: burst=3, rate=3/15 min per IP → Retry-After: 300 s\nRate limiter fires AFTER JWT middleware — all rate-limit requests must carry a valid token.\n\nEnvironment variables required:\n  bootstrap_secret   — must match BOOTSTRAP_SECRET in the running server's .env\n  gmail_test_email   — Gmail address for OTP receipt\n  gmail_access_token — OAuth2 token for Gmail API reads\n\nAll test users use @e2e.test addresses or gmail_test_email.\nRun `make _e2e-db-clean` and `make _e2e-kv-clean` before each suite run.\n\nNotes on what is NOT covered here (covered by internal tests):\n  - user_not_found → 404                          — handler_test.go (requires authenticated ghost user;\n                                                     untestable via black-box e2e since a valid JWT\n                                                     cannot be issued for a non-existent account)\n  - email_not_verified → 422 email_not_verified    — service_test.go / handler_test.go\n                                                     Not testable via black-box e2e: an unverified user\n                                                     cannot log in to obtain a JWT.\n  - Inactive user account → 422 user_not_active    — service_test.go + store_test.go\n  - BootstrapOwnerTx / DB failures → 500           — service_test.go\n  - All error responses carry code + JSON CT       — handler_test.go",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "event": [
    {
      "listen": "prerequest",
      "script": {
        "type": "text/javascript",
        "exec": [
          "// Increment the request sequence counter and derive a unique X-Forwarded-For IP",
          "// for every request so non-RL folders never exhaust any rate-limit bucket.",
          "// The rate-limiting folder overrides _xff to 127.0.0.1 via its own prerequest.",
          "// Requires TRUSTED_PROXIES=127.0.0.1/32 in .env.",
          "const n = (pm.collectionVariables.get('_req_seq') | 0) + 1;",
          "pm.collectionVariables.set('_req_seq', n);",
          "const ip = '10.' + ((n>>16)&0xff) + '.' + ((n>>8)&0xff) + '.' + (n&0xff);",
          "pm.collectionVariables.set('_xff', ip);"
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "setup",
      "description": "Registers the gmail_test_email user, fetches the OTP from Gmail, verifies email, logs in, and calls GET /me to capture bstrp_access_token and bstrp_happy_id.\n\nbstrp_access_token is required by every subsequent folder (the endpoint now requires JWT auth).\nbstrp_happy_id is captured from GET /me body.id — this is the authenticated caller whose user ID the service will use.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "POST /register → 201 (setup owner candidate)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const email = pm.environment.get('gmail_test_email');",
                  "if (!email) {",
                  "    console.error('[ERROR] gmail_test_email not set in environment — add it to environment.json.');",
                  "}",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('bstrp_happy_email', email);",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('bstrp_happy_password', 'P@ssw0rd1!');"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 201', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                  "pm.test('message field present and non-empty', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().message).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty);",
                  "",
                  "const token = pm.variables.get('gmail_access_token');",
                  "if (!token) { console.warn('[WARN] gmail_access_token not set — skipping Gmail fetch'); return; }",
                  "",
                  "console.log('[INFO] Waiting 8 s for verification email to arrive in Gmail...');",
                  "const start = Date.now();",
                  "while (Date.now() - start < 8000) {}",
                  "console.log('[INFO] Done waiting. Querying Gmail API (async)...');",
                  "",
                  "const query = encodeURIComponent('subject:\"Verify your\" newer_than:1h');",
                  "pm.sendRequest({",
                  "    url: 'https://gmail.googleapis.com/gmail/v1/users/me/messages?q=' + query + '&maxResults=3',",
                  "    method: 'GET',",
                  "    header: { Authorization: 'Bearer ' + token }",
                  "}, (err, res) => {",
                  "    if (err) { console.error('[ERROR] Gmail list failed:', err); return; }",
                  "    if (res.code === 401) { console.error('[ERROR] Gmail token expired — refresh at https://developers.google.com/oauthplayground'); return; }",
                  "    const msgs = res.json().messages;",
                  "    if (!msgs || !msgs.length) { console.warn('[WARN] No matching email found in Gmail.'); return; }",
                  "    pm.sendRequest({",
                  "        url: 'https://gmail.googleapis.com/gmail/v1/users/me/messages/' + msgs[0].id + '?format=full',",
                  "        method: 'GET',",
                  "        header: { Authorization: 'Bearer ' + token }",
                  "    }, (err2, res2) => {",
                  "        if (err2) { console.error('[ERROR] Gmail fetch failed:', err2); return; }",
                  "        const msg = res2.json();",
                  "        let body = '';",
                  "        const parts = msg.payload && msg.payload.parts;",
                  "        if (parts && parts.length) {",
                  "            const p = parts.find(x => x.mimeType === 'text/plain') || parts.find(x => x.mimeType === 'text/html');",
                  "            if (p && p.body && p.body.data) body = atob(p.body.data.replace(/-/g, '+').replace(/_/g, '/'));",
                  "        } else if (msg.payload && msg.payload.body && msg.payload.body.data) {",
                  "            body = atob(msg.payload.body.data.replace(/-/g, '+').replace(/_/g, '/'));",
                  "        }",
                  "        if (!body) { console.warn('[WARN] Could not decode email body.'); return; }",
                  "        const match = body.match(/(?<!#)\\b(\\d{6})\\b/);",
                  "        if (!match) { console.warn('[WARN] No 6-digit OTP found in email body.'); return; }",
                  "        pm.collectionVariables.set('bstrp_code', match[1]);",
                  "        console.log('[INFO] OTP stored in collection variable \"bstrp_code\":', match[1]);",
                  "    });",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "X-Forwarded-For", "value": "{{_xff}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\"display_name\": \"BstrpOwner\", \"email\": \"{{bstrp_happy_email}}\", \"password\": \"{{bstrp_happy_password}}\"}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/register",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "register"]
            }
          }
        },
