    {
      "name": "rate-limiting",
      "description": "Verifies the bstrp:ip: IP rate limiter (burst=3, rate=3/15 min per IP → 1 token/300 s). The folder prerequest pins _xff to 127.0.0.1 so all requests share one bucket.\n\nIMPORTANT: The rate limiter fires AFTER JWTAuth middleware. All requests must carry a valid access token to reach the limiter — requests without a token return 401 before the limiter is checked.\n\n3 warmup requests drain the burst capacity (each returns 409 since an owner already exists — owner check fires before any DB mutation). The 4th must return 429 with code=too_many_requests and Retry-After: 300.\n\nRequires TRUSTED_PROXIES=127.0.0.1/32 in .env and Redis flushed (make _e2e-kv-clean) before this folder.",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "prerequest",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "// Override the collection-level unique IP so every request in this",
              "// folder shares the 127.0.0.1 bucket and exhausts it together.",
              "pm.collectionVariables.set('_xff', '127.0.0.1');"
